Program: Great Lives
Title: Flora Sandes
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0076hd1
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 13 Mar 2015
Kate Adie discusses Flora Sandes, Britain's first commissioned female officer in World War One. With Humphrey Carpenter. From February 2003. The biographical series in which a distinguished guest chooses someone who's inspired their life. Will their hero stand up to intensive scrutiny and merit the description of having led a great life? From 2003. Show less